==English==

===Expression===
'''[[thank you]] [[very]] [[much]]'''

# Said to express greater gratitude than would be conveyed by [[thank you]].
# ''(less common) A [[sarcastic]] [[thank you]].
#*'''2005:''' [[w:Halle Berry|Halle Berry]], at the [[w:Razzie|Razzie Awards]] [[2005]], ''Acceptance speech for Worst Actress award for her part in Catwoman'' - ["Thanking" a French director of ''Catwoman''] '''Thank you very much'''. ... I didn't know what the hell he was saying -- it sure showed in my performance. 

